org.threadly.load

Class ParameterStore

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.threadly.load.ParameterStore
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ScriptFactory, ScriptRunner

    public class ParameterStore
extends java.lang.Object

    Storage for parameters, providing a common interface for retriving them. Properties will be provided after construction and can be accessed via getIntValue(String), getIntValue(String, int), getLongValue(String), getLongValue(String, long), getDoubleValue(String), getDoubleValue(String, double), getStringValue(String) and getStringValue(String, String).

      • parseProperties

        public static java.util.Properties parseProperties(java.lang.String[] args,
                                                   int offset,
                                                   int length)
        Parse the parameters from an array of String arguments. It is expected that each String be in the format of key=value. Any '=' signs in the keys or values are unexpected and may cause issues.
        Parameters:
        args - Array of arguments to parse through
        offset - Offset into array to start parsing from
        length - Number of elements which should be inspected
        Returns:
        New properties reference which has the parsed out key/values

      • getPossibleParameters

        public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> getPossibleParameters()
        This is an optional function to override. It is highly recommended it is overridden if using ScriptRunner. This provides documentation for what parameters are used by this builder. If someone fails to provide a parameter this will be displayed to the CLI so that it makes it easier to know what was missing. This is triggered by throwing ParameterStore.ParameterException. This map is structured such that the key represents the parameter key. The value is an optional description to describe what the key represents.
        Returns:
        Map with keys that indicate the parameters used, and values representing their description

      • getBoolValue

        public boolean getBoolValue(java.lang.String key)
        Returns a boolean value parameter for the given key. If no value for the given key is found, a ParameterStore.ParameterException will be thrown. If the parameter may or may not exist use getBoolValue(String, boolean). If unable to parse the boolean for the key a ParameterStore.ParameterException. It is expected that the string value to represent the boolean will be either "true" or "false".
        Parameters:
        key - Key to lookup the boolean value from
        Returns:
        Boolean parameter value or the provided default if none is found

If unable to parse the integer for the key a ParameterStore.ParameterException will be thrown with a NumberFormatException being the cause.
